<BaseLayout title="Data Use and Licensing | CourtScope"><section class="hero"><div class="prose-width"><p class="eyebrow">Public policy</p><h1>Data Use and Licensing</h1><p class="lede">Every dataset carries its own source, provenance, privacy, and reuse terms.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="prose-width"><div class="card"><p>CourtScope code is AGPL-3.0. Court records and derived datasets may have different rights and restrictions. Download pages identify attribution, redistribution, commercial-use, and prohibited-use rules for each release.</p><h2>What controls</h2><p>Official source terms, applicable law, dataset-specific notices, and the current published CourtScope methodology control where they are more specific. Contact <a href="mailto:info@courtscope.org">info@courtscope.org</a> for questions.</p><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 11, 2026</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>